>>
>> We don't map all per-cpu areas, but only the per-cpu variables we need. ASI
>> code uses the per-cpu cpu_asi_session variable which is mapped when an ASI
>> is created (see patch 15/26):
> 
> No fair!  I had per-cpu variables just for PTI at some point and had to
> give them up! ;)
> 
>> +Â Â Â  /*
>> +Â Â Â Â  * Map the percpu ASI sessions. This is used by interrupt handlers
>> +Â Â Â Â  * to figure out if we have entered isolation and switch back to
>> +Â Â Â Â  * the kernel address space.
>> +Â Â Â Â  */
>> +Â Â Â  err = ASI_MAP_CPUVAR(asi, cpu_asi_session);
>> +Â Â Â  if (err)
>> +Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  return err;
